	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I second that. When I started to program my emulator, I knew pretty much nothing, and because of that it was a good 4-5 months before I could even get the CPU up and running to about 90% of what it is now.
<br />
<br />If you insist on writing a NES emulator then write a 6502 emulator. Forget the NES specifics, just write one on it's own and see how far you get.
<br />
<br />Here is the best 6502 resource on the net.
<br />
<br /><a href="http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/index.html" class="postlink">http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/index.html</a>

		

