		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">"third class" NES emulators floating around which nobody ever uses</div>
<br />
<br />As the author of a third class NES emulator that nobody uses <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />, I'm going to have to disagree with this point.
<br />
<br />Sure, my emulator doesn't do anything better (and many things worse) than other emulators, but I learned a ton of stuff, and had a lot of fun, while writing it.  I still remember the first time I got a real game -- Arkanoid -- to run on it.  Can't beat that feeling.
<br />
<br />I completely agree that this isn't a good beginner's project, but I never really understood the 'yours isn't going to be any better than what's out there already' argument.  That's just not what it's about for me.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
