		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />(Laughs and Laughs and Laughs...)
<br />
<br />A 6502 is CPU that the NES uses. ROMs contain both code and graphics data and when you load the ROM into it's memory it runs the code from memory. You can us any programming language you want but C/C++ IS the best since almost all emulators use it.
<br />
<br />Since you seem to know just about nothing, I would strongly recommend reading up on the 6502 for a very long time before starting to write anything. Make sure you understand everything first.

		

